
[1]defamation

   DEFAMATION, n. The uttering of slanderous words with a view to injure
   anothers reputation; the malicious uttering of falsehood respecting
   another which tends to destroy or impair his good name, character or
   occupation; slander; calumny. To constitute defamation in law, the
   words must be false and spoken maliciously. Defamatory words written
   and published are called a libel.
